The paper deals with the formal specification and analysis of autonomous systems, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. The use of probabilistic model checking suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO), while the consideration of non-functional requirements and the exploration of system capabilities aligns with software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of formal methods and lattice theory suggests a connection to logic in computer science (cs.LO).
